explanation: The provided solution utilizes a HashMap for O(1) lookups and a doubly linked list to track the order of elements. When an element is accessed or updated, it is moved to the front of the list. When the cache is full and a new element is added, the least recently used element (the one at the end of the list) is removed. This approach ensures that both get and put operations have an average time complexity of O(1).

